Message.Title: What We Know Now
Message.Msg: What we know now is that the ARM era is ending faster than we thought. A body blow is not a knock-out punch but as the fight goes on, body blows take the legs out of the fighter. A series of body blows has the same effect as a knock-out punch. Intel is now delivering body blows with greater regularity: Altera. The first body blow and a terribly effective one. The crowd gasped. Silvermont. More like a series of effective jabs, driving ARM back across the ring. Intel Samsung Tablet. Like a strong left hook coming out of no where, this punch left the crowd wondering if ARM was dead on its feet with eyes glazed over. And now we can see the next one coming: Haswell. ARM can clearly see it coming as well but because of the previous body blows, doesn't seem to be able to dance out of the way. The legs are gone.
